<br>
That was 3 years ago.  Since then, we had another miscarriage.  But last July we had a healthy baby girl.  Her name is Phoebe.<br>
<br>
We have Audrey's picture (taken after she was still-born, the nurses cleaned her up, put a diaper on her, wrapped her up in a receving blanket, and let us say goodbye) on the wall in the hallway.  And we make sure Phoebe say goodnight to her sister every night.  &quot;Who's that?  Yeah, that's your sister Audrey and she loves Korean pears.  Say good night sister.&quot;<br>
<br>
Had Audrey lived, our lives would have been very different, probably difficult and painful.  But that's what parenthood is.  Its the good, the bad, the ugly, the joy, the sadness, the laugh, and the disaster.  The little ones didn't ask to be born, we did.  So we'll take every responsibility and baggage that comes with her.  And I would not give up a minute of it.<br>
<br>
I have always been pro-choice.  And I choose life. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tryonb>TryonB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 250<br> <font color=#330000>(8/8/03 9:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=933.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To let live or to euthanize? (kinda NSFW, no porn)</span><hr size=1> It's so nice to see a post in the rant section make it to page 2 without a flamefest.  Kudos!<br>
<br>
My first reaction was with the majority here, best to end it's life and save it from a short life of pain.  But then I got to thinking about it a little and I'm torn.  The child is born this way, thus has no basis of comparison of what a normal life is supposed to be.  I'm sure the pain is there, but since this feeling is all the child knows there might be a chance to, for lack of a better term, get used to it.  The child might become accustomed to it and learn to forget about it.  While that in and of itself is tragic, we don't really know what goes on in the minds of these victims.  Call me crazy, but after looking at the picture and getting over the initial horror of the grotesqueness, I can actually see a happy child inside.  He's wearing some spiffy shorts and appears to be trying to smile, seriously.  While he in no way lead a normal life, normal is what we make of it.  The child doesn't know what a normal life is.  If there is any possible way to bring joy to it, somehow...if faced with the decision I <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>might</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> chose to let it live just to see it try to smile once.  I've never fathered a child though, so I truely don't know. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=idadar1337>Idadar1337</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.everlore.com/GFILES/UserPic67062_13144.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>T3h 1337 0n3</span><br>  Posts: 624<br> <font color=#330000>(8/8/03 9:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=933.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.hot.ee/raadius/tatu.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To let live or to euthanize? (kinda NSFW, no porn)</span><hr size=1>