I always remember hearing stories of these kids who were so full of life and hope, yet they couldn't run, play, or do anything of the sort.  I can not describe to you how ashamed I felt of myself many times.  I would have a bad week and go in there and they would be ready to hug me and tell me how they had such a great week they only had to go through 2 radation treatments and they still have most of their hair!  Or they were allowed to start eating solid foods again, how wonderful lime jello tastes to them!  They were so happy over the little things.  I think the only reason their parents made it through everything was the life and joy these ill children brought to them.  It was very hard to come in and see empty beds knowing they were not empty because the children went home well but empty because they passed away.<br>
I asked one of the parents if they had to do it over again would they have gone through eveything.  They said yes without even thinking about it, they said had they not gone through all the pain the memories of all the joy wouldn't seem nearly as wonderful and they knew that their lives would have been empty without the love of that child.  And how blessed they felt that they were allowed to love someone so wonderful even if it was only for a few years.<br>
<br>
I could never throw away a human life without a second thought.  I could never look at my unborn child and say you are not fit to live.  You never know when the doctor could be wrong on a test.  <br>
Maybe being a religious person I view this in another light.  I belive everything happens for a purpose, and no matter how disfigured or horrid it may seem to some, that life was allowed to happen for a reason. (go ahead and flame my values if you like) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mausoleumthenecro>Mausoleum the Necro</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Opinionated Asshole</span><br>  Posts: 517<br> <font color=#330000>(8/8/03 10:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=933.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To let live or to euthanize? (kinda NSFW, no porn)</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>This is hard for me to think about. I have been told I can't have Kids (also hard to think about). So I tend to think that I would want any child that I might be able to have. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
